$ Oracle: Init parameter AUDIT_TRAIL
@ audit_trail

The value of `audit_trail` is effective only when using *traditional auditing* (which was deprecated in → development/databases/Oracle/Releases-and-versions/21c and desupported in → development/databases/Oracle/Releases-and-versions/23c[23ai]).

The value of `audit_trail` can be set to
table { ll
  `none` ☰
  `os` ☰
  `db` ☰ Populates `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/base-tables/aud`
  `db,extended` ☰ Also fills values for `sqltext` and `sqlbind` in `aud$`
  `xml` ☰
  `xml,extended` ☰
table }


sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters
